find /home/user/experiments -type f \( -name '*.pt' -o -name '*.pth' \) -size +1G -exec ls -lh {} \;

Or for just listing paths: find /home/user/experiments -type f \( -name '*.pt' -o -name '*.pth' \) -size +1G

To also see sizes sorted: find /home/user/experiments -type f \( -name '*.pt' -o -name '*.pth' \) -size +1G -exec ls -lh {} \; | sort -k5 -hr
